Halve, peel and thinly slice the @onion{1}.

Drain and rinse the @black beans{1%carton} in a #sieve{}. Transfer half to a
#small bowl{} and roughly mash them using a #potato masher{} or the back of a
#fork{}.

Peel and grate the @garlic{2%cloves} (or use a #garlic press{}).

Heat a drizzle of @oil{2%tbsp} in a large #saucepan{} on medium-high heat.

Add the onion to the #pan{} and stir-fry until softened, ~{4-5%minutes}.

Stir in the garlic and @smoked paprika{1%sachet}. Cook until fragrant,
~{1%minute}.

Add the @tomato passata{1%carton}, black beans (both mashed and whole),
@vegetable stock paste{15%g}, @honey{1%tbsp} and @water{100%ml} for the soup
(see pantry for both amounts) to the saucepan.

Stir to combine and bring to the boil. Lower the heat to medium and simmer until
thickened, ~{5-6%minutes}.

Meanwhile, preheat your #grill{} to high.

Halve the @ciabatta{1}, then cut into 1cm slices. Grate the
@mature cheddar cheese{40%g}.

Pop the ciabatta slices onto a medium #baking tray{}. Sprinkle over the cheese
and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Grill on the top shelf until melted and golden, ~{3-5%minutes}.

While the ciabatta grills, drain the @sweetcorn{160%g}.

Stir the @creme fraiche{75%g}, corn, @chipotle paste{20%g}
(add less if you'd prefer things milder) and @butter{20%g} through the soup
until combined. Bring to the boil, then remove from the heat.

Taste and season with salt and pepper if needed. Add a splash of water if it's
a little thick.

Share the soup between your #bowls{}.

Serve the cheesy toasts alongside for dipping and scooping. Enjoy!

